<div style="border: double 5px #89043d; background:#eaebed; padding-left: 10px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; margin-left: 15%; margin-right: 15%; line-height: 0.75">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1 id="toc0"><span>Latest Episode</span></h1>
<h2 id="toc1"><span>Episode 4: No Clue, No Problem</span></h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:120%;"><strong><a href="https://redcircle.com/shows/5af1a111-e948-475f-9f7d-913f572ddd88/episodes/bbf50adf-72f6-4b02-8b69-be021c913361" target="_blank">Listen to the episode here!</a></strong></span></p>
<p>The gang search the city for a Way into the Wanderer's Library. Eustace &quot;borrows&quot; a Library Card. Troy is mistaken for a Jehovah's Witness. Lacy knows what cocaine smells like.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center; font-size: 120%;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;+</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;-</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="text-align: left; font-size: 83%;">
<p><strong>Mentioned or Appearing in Play</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The International Center for the Study of Unified Thaumatology (ICSUT) is a recurring Group of Interest throughout the Third Law Canon; the ICSUT Portlands campus first appears in <strong><a href="/vital-signs">Vital Signs</a></strong>, by <em>GreenWolf</em>.</li>
<li>The Wanderer's Library is a major recurring location in the Foundationverse. It first appears in Third Law in <strong><a href="/under-control">Under Control</a></strong>, by <em>TyGently</em>, and also features in <strong><a href="/the-dedekind-infinite-demographic">The Dedekind Infinite Demographic</a></strong>, by <em>Taffeta</em>.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/rainbow-crapitalism">More Like Rainbow Crapitalism</a></strong> is a tale by <em>ch00bakka</em> and <em>kinchtheknifeblade</em>.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/scp-2602">SCP-2602, which used to be a library</a></strong>, by <em>Communism will win</em>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mentioned During the Break</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/whats-going-down">Everybody Look What's Going Down</a></strong>, by <em>ch00bakka</em>.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/australian-rules">Australian Rules Drag Racing</a></strong>, by <em>ch00bakka</em>.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/thorne-is-born">A Thorne Is Born</a></strong>, by <em>GreenWolf</em>.</li>
<li><strong><a href="/the-powers-that-bark">The Powers That Bark</a></strong>, by <em>TyGently</em> and <em>A Random Day</em>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="Intro"></a></p>
<div style="border: solid 5px #999999; background:#f5fefe; padding: 10px; padding-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1 id="toc2"><span>Introduction</span></h1>
</div>
<p>It's 1996, and the dream of the 90s is already dead in Three Portlands.</p>
<p>With the new millennium only a few years away, the Golden Age of Normalcy is over. The paratech industry is in shambles, paracrime is on the rise, and Bill Clinton is President. Nowhere are these things more apparent than in Three Portlands – its economy is in ruins, racketeers have overrun the Docks District, and the city council is paralyzed by nonpartisan infighting.</p>
<p>Frustrated by the inaction of the city government, Alderman Stephen McClure has resorted to extralegal methods of resolving the numerous crises that threaten the city. Working in secret to bypass the deadlocked City Council, he has assembled a ragtag group of misfits and meddlers to help fix Portlands. Operating without official backing or authority, they will have to contend with the multitude of corporations, cults, cabals, conspiracies, and cartels that all have their own agendas for the city.</p>
<p>But bad things happen to those who attempt to tame the Weird City. And the storm is just getting started.</p>
</div>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<a name="Episodes"></a></p>
<div style="border: solid 5px #999999; background:#f5fefe; padding: 10px; padding-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h1 id="toc3"><span>Episodes</span></h1>
</div>
<p><a name="E1"></a></p>
<div style="border: double 5px #89043d; background:#eaebed; padding: 10px; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 0;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h2 id="toc4"><span>Episode 1: The Alderman's Army</span></h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:120%;"><strong><a href="https://redcircle.com/shows/5af1a111-e948-475f-9f7d-913f572ddd88/episodes/f8ae095d-245b-40fc-b275-81ec24135926" target="_blank">Listen to the episode here!</a></strong></span></p>
<p>The gang are invited to a New Year's Eve party, where Stephen McClure asks for their help in forestalling an impending humanitarian disaster. Eustace does terrible things with a mouse. Troy punches a garbage bin. Lacy looks for quarters.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center; font-size: 120%;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;+</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;-</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="text-align: left; font-size: 83%;">
<p><strong>Mentioned in the Intro</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The <strong><a href="/third-law-hub">Third Law Canon</a></strong> is by various authors, with the hub and continuity maintained by <em>GreenWolf</em></li>
<li><strong><a href="/three-portlands-hub">Three Portlands</a></strong> first appeared in <a href="/the-analog-kid">The Analog Kid</a>, by <em>GreenWolf</em>, who also wrote the hub</li>
<li><strong><a href="/scp-2206">SCP-2206</a> - &quot;Maximum League Baseball&quot;</strong> - By <em>GreenWolf</em></li>
<li><strong><a href="/task-forces#tau-5">MTF Tau-5 (&quot;Samsara&quot;)</a></strong> was created during the <a href="/mobile-task-force-contest">2016 Mobile Task Force Contest</a>, by <em>A Random Day</em>, <em>TyGently</em>, <em>GreenWolf</em>, and <em>sirpudding</em></li>
<li>Eustace Rowe first appeared in <a href="/under-control">Under Control</a> and features prominently in <strong><a href="/comedown-machine-hub">Comedown Machine</a></strong>, both by <em>TyGently</em></li>
<li><strong><a href="/scp-2624">SCP-2624</a> - &quot;Laika's Sweetheart Space-Beacon&quot;</strong> - By <em>TyGently</em></li>
<li><strong><a href="/scp-3900">SCP-3900</a> - &quot;The Internet of Things That Are Wolves&quot;</strong> - By <em>TyGently</em></li>
<li>The <strong><a href="/deer-college-hub">Deer College</a></strong> Group of Interest was originally created by <em>ch00bakka</em>, first appearing in <a href="/about-deer">About Deer College</a></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Mentioned or Appearing in Play</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Jordan Raybon first appeared in <strong><a href="/when-parallel-lines-diverge">When Parallel Lines Diverge</a></strong>, by <em>Jacob Conwell</em> and <em>GreenWolf</em></li>
<li>The City of Doors first appeared in <strong><a href="/preliminary-report">Preliminary Report of J.C. Randall</a></strong>, by <em>GreenWolf</em></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="E2"></a></p>
<div style="border: double 5px #89043d; background:#eaebed; padding: 10px; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 0;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h2 id="toc5"><span>Episode 2: Plan C for Catapult</span></h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:120%;"><strong><a href="https://redcircle.com/shows/5af1a111-e948-475f-9f7d-913f572ddd88/episodes/3e7bc481-efe5-4934-a585-4ff2c7372945" target="_blank">Listen to the episode here!</a></strong></span></p>
<p>The gang investigate the Trolley Yards, where they meet the mysterious Cinnabar, who is <em>not</em> a raccoon. Eustace is recognized. Troy is overly optimistic. Lacy suggests a projectile solution.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center; font-size: 120%;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;+</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;-</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="text-align: left; font-size: 83%;">
<p><strong>Mentioned or Appearing in Play</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/serpent-s-hand-hub">The Serpent's Hand</a></strong> Group of Interest, by various authors. Notable appearances of the Serpent's Hand in Third Law include <a href="/the-lord-of-endowments">The Lord of Endowments</a> by <em>sirpudding</em>, <a href="/barrels-of-prose">Barrels of Prose and Slugs of Pulp</a> by <em>NatVoltaic</em>, and <a href="/unicorn-horn">Unicorn Horn</a> by <em>GreenWolf</em>.</li>
<li>More information about Observers, Constructed Intelligences, and Elan-Vital Energy can be found in the Thaumatology Seminar series (<strong><a href="/goc-supplemental-thaumatology">Part One</a></strong>, <strong><a href="/goc-supplemental-arad">Part Two</a></strong>, <strong><a href="/goc-supplemental-thaumworkings">Part Three</a></strong>) from the <a href="/goc-hub-page">GOC Casefiles</a>, by <em>DrClef</em>. These provide much of the background on the magic system used in Third Law.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="E3"></a></p>
<div style="border: double 5px #89043d; background:#eaebed; padding: 10px; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 0;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h2 id="toc6"><span>Episode 3: The Portrait in the Attic</span></h2>
</div>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size:120%;"><strong><a href="https://redcircle.com/shows/5af1a111-e948-475f-9f7d-913f572ddd88/episodes/254cf92a-f906-45cb-9494-aca1210560a0" target="_blank">Listen to the episode here!</a></strong></span></p>
<p>The gang go to Golemancy United to open negotiations with the guild's enforcer. Eustace bluffs a rock. Troy hears a confession. Lacy steals a shoe.</p>
<hr />
<div style="text-align: center; font-size: 120%;">
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;+</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Mentioned&nbsp;in&nbsp;this&nbsp;Episode&nbsp;-</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div style="text-align: left; font-size: 83%;">
<p><strong>Mentioned or Appearing in Play</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Golemancy United first appeared in <strong><a href="/under-control">Under Control</a></strong>, by <em>TyGently</em>.</li>
<li>The Third Law interpretation of Mr. Dark is presented in <strong><a href="/when-situations-degenerate">When Situations Degenerate</a></strong>, by <em>ch00bakka</em>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><a name="E4"></a></p>
<div style="border: double 5px #89043d; background:#eaebed; padding: 10px; padding-bottom: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 0;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h2 id="toc7"><span>Episode 4: No Clue, No Problem</span></h2>
